# Storefront Overhaul — Cart, Product Details, Navigation, Theme & New Pages

Comprehensive refactoring of the ecommerce platform addressing cart simplification, product detail cleanup, admin shipping management, dynamic logos, search functionality, theme consistency, and new page creation.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Shipping Cost Model**: You want shipping cost to be quantity-based and set from admin. I'll create a shipping configuration where admin sets a **per-item shipping cost** (e.g., ৳30/item × 3 items = ৳90). Should it instead be tiered (e.g., 1-5 items = ৳60, 6-10 items = ৳100), or is per-item sufficient?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Discount Model**: Currently `salePrice` exists on each product (set by admin in product edit). Should I also add a **global discount** (e.g., admin sets 10% off all products) in a separate admin settings page? Or is per-product `salePrice` enough?

> [!WARNING]
> **Login/Signup Pages**: Currently auth is Google-only via popup modal. Creating dedicated `/login` and `/signup` pages — should these still be Google-only, or do you want email/password signup too? (Email/password would require Firebase Email Auth setup.)

## Open Questions

1. **Wishlist persistence** — Should wishlists persist in Firestore (requiring login) or localStorage (per device, no login needed)?
2. **Footer content** — The footer currently has Etsy branding (e.g., "Etsy blog", "Sell on Etsy"). Should I replace all these with generic placeholder links, or should admin manage footer links too?
3. **Logo formats** — You mention navbar logo (wide/text) and footer logo (icon). Should admin upload these two separately, or one logo used everywhere? Plan assumes two separate logo slots (navbar + footer).

